  "calendarNotes": "Winston-Salem/Forsyth County Schools begins the 2026–2027 school year on August 10, 2026 — two weeks earlier than Charlotte-Mecklenburg and Guilford County, starting on August 25 and August 24, respectively. WSFCS adopted a modified-start calendar so high school students can finish first-semester exams before winter break instead of after returning in January. Spring Break runs March 26–April 2, 2027. The school year ends May 21, 2027 — earlier than Charlotte-Mecklenburg, Wake County, and Guilford County, all of which finish in early June."
